ing lands and brilliant cities of South
America —to tropical Ecuador, ancient
Peru, legendary Bolivia -
- to sparkling
Santiago and sophisticated Buenos Aires.
Romantic names
that come alive as
you wing along the direct Panagra Route
down South America's west coast. You skirt
the Andes, leap the Equator in the wink of
aneye—cradledin great American planes,
operating on fast and frequent schedules.
Rates are surprisingly low. And there
are economical all-expense cruises rang-
ing from a week in Inca-land to 3 to 8
weeks 'round South America. Combination
air-sea trips may also be arranged.
Write our New York office for free
booklet, illustrated in full color, called
"The Panagra Route." For additional in-
formation consult your travel agent, any
airline office or any Pan
American Airways office.
